# Quick Integration - GitHub File Manager

## Step 1: Copy Files

Copy the entire `github-file-manager` folder to your project root:

```bash
cp -r /mnt/okcomputer/output/github-file-manager /path/to/your/project/
```

## Step 2: Install Dependency

```bash
npm install axios
```

## Step 3: Modify server.js

Add these lines to your `server.js` file:

```javascript
// Add at the top with other requires
const { initGitHubModule } = require('./github-file-manager/server/github-server-init');

// Add after creating your Express app (after: const app = express();)
// Initialize GitHub File Manager
initGitHubModule(app);
```

## Step 4: Modify index.html

Add these lines to your `index.html` file in the `<head>` section:

```html
<!-- GitHub File Manager CSS -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/github-file-manager/css/github-file-manager.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/github-file-manager/css/file-viewer.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/github-file-manager/css/dialogs.css">
```

Add these lines before your main app script in `<body>`:

```html
<!-- GitHub File Manager JavaScript -->
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/github/github-api-client.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/github/github-state-manager.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/ui/github-panel-ui.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/ui/file-viewer-ui.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/ui/properties-dialog-ui.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/ui/delete-dialog-ui.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/ui/rename-dialog-ui.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/features/transfer-system.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/features/viewport-stability.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/features/delete-stability-handler.js"></script>
<script src="/github-file-manager/js/github-file-manager.js"></script>
```

## Step 5: Modify index.html - Add GitHub Panel

Find your dual-panel layout and add the GitHub panel container. If you have a layout like:

```html
<div class="workspace">
  <div class="storage-panel">...</div>
</div>
```

Change it to:

```html
<div class="workspace">
  <div class="storage-panel">...</div>
  <div class="github-panel" id="githubPanelContainer"></div>
</div>
```

## Step 6: Modify main.js

Add this to your main JavaScript file (where you initialize your app):

```javascript
// After your app initialization
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', async () => {
  // ... your existing init code ...
  
  // Initialize GitHub File Manager
  try {
    await githubFileManager.init('githubPanelContainer');
    console.log('GitHub File Manager initialized');
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed to initialize GitHub File Manager:', error);
  }
});
```

## Step 7: Start Your Server

```bash
node server.js
```

## Step 8: Authenticate

1. Open your app in browser
2. In the GitHub panel, enter your GitHub Personal Access Token
3. Click "Connect"

### Creating a GitHub Token:

1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
3. Give it a name like "File Manager"
4. Select scope: `repo` (for private repos) or `public_repo` (for public only)
5. Click "Generate token"
6. Copy the token and paste it in the app

## That's It!

Your GitHub File Manager is now integrated. You can:
- Browse repositories
- Navigate files and folders
- View and edit files
- Transfer files between Storage and GitHub
- Delete and rename files
- View file properties and history

## Troubleshooting

### "Cannot find module 'axios'"
Run: `npm install axios`

### "404 on /api/github/*"
Make sure you added `initGitHubModule(app)` in server.js

### "GitHub panel not showing"
Check that the element with id "githubPanelContainer" exists in your HTML

### "CSS not loading"
Verify the CSS paths are correct relative to your server root

