## Design Philosophy

### GitHub as Storage
Users interact with GitHub repositories exactly like they manage files in a file manager:
- No commits visible to users
- No branches exposed as concepts
- No version control complexity
- Just files, folders, and paths

### Universal Transfer
A single "Transfer" operation handles all file movements:
- Storage → GitHub
- GitHub → Storage
- Direction determined automatically

### Mobile-First Stability
The interface remains stable on mobile browsers:
- No zoom on input focus
- No layout shifts
- Desktop-like experience
- Native file manager feel

## Browser Support

- Chrome 80+
- Firefox 75+
- Safari 13+
- Edge 80+

## Security

- Tokens stored server-side
- All API calls proxied through your server
- No client-side GitHub API access
- Configurable token encryption

